## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is the cheapest Blue Nile engagement ring under $5,000?

The cheapest complete preset engagement ring at Blue Nile is the [Round 1ct Lab-Grown Petite Solitaire in 14K Yellow Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/diamond-preset/round-1-ct-certified-lab-grown-diamond-petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-296973?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) at $1,490. It includes a certified 1ct lab-grown diamond already set in the ring — no separate stone purchase needed.

### Can I get a natural diamond engagement ring under $5,000 at Blue Nile?

Yes. Natural diamond presets start at $3,380 for a 1ct round petite solitaire in 14K white or yellow gold. The highest-end natural preset under $5,000 is the French Pavé in platinum at $4,570. All natural presets in this price range are GIA-certified 1ct stones.

### How big of a diamond can I get under $5,000 at Blue Nile?

For lab-grown diamonds: up to 2.5ct oval or round. The Oval 2.5ct Lab-Grown Petite Twist in white gold is $4,580 and the Round 2.5ct Lab Riviera Pavé is $4,390. For natural diamonds: the maximum is 1ct — no natural diamond preset over 1ct is available under $5,000.

### Are Blue Nile preset rings certified?

Yes. All Blue Nile preset engagement rings include a GIA or equivalent grading certificate. The certificate confirms the diamond's carat weight, color, clarity, and cut grade.

### What is the difference between preset and design-your-own at Blue Nile?

A preset ring comes with the diamond already included and set — one purchase, ready to ship. A design-your-own ring requires you to choose a setting separately and then select a loose diamond, which is then set. Presets are simpler and often more affordable for buyers who don't need a custom stone specification.

### Is lab-grown worth it under $5,000 at Blue Nile?

The math is straightforward: lab-grown gives you 2–2.5× more carat weight for the same dollar as natural. The only trade-off is resale value — natural diamonds hold value better than lab-grown. If resale is not a factor, lab-grown presets deliver significantly more size and setting quality per dollar.
